-- Northrop gets $1.45 billion for Navy amphibious ship
-- 
-- Mon Nov 6, 2006 5:56pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/11/06/us-arms-northrop-navy-idUSWAT00653320061106

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Northrop Grumman Ship Systems ( NOC.N ) has been awarded a $1.45 billion contract modification for building LPD 17 Class amphibious transport dock ships, the U.S. Navy said on Monday. 

 The award includes building an eighth ship and preparing for construction of a ninth ship, the Pentagon said in a statement.